      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Limitations and Practical Constraints"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Late chunking requires a long-context encoder that exposes per-token representations \u2014 most API embedding services (OpenAI, Cohere) only return a single pooled vector per call and cannot be used. Self-hosted models like jina-embeddings-v2 or nomic-embed-text-v1.5 are the practical options. A second constraint is throughput: encoding a full document as a single sequence is slower than batching many small chunks in parallel, so indexing throughput is lower."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Model requirement: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "must expose last_hidden_state token vectors, not just [CLS] pooled output."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Context limit: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "documents longer than the model's max tokens must still be split at a coarser level (e.g., by section) before late chunking within each section."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Throughput: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "encode one document at a time rather than batching chunks \u2014 mitigate by parallelising document-level encoding across workers."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Compatibility: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "query encoding must use the same model without late chunking \u2014 encode each user query as a standard single-vector embedding."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Late Chunking with the Jina API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Jina AI's embedding API (api.jina.ai) natively supports late chunking via a `late_chunking=True` request parameter. The API accepts the full document text, applies the long-context encoder internally, and returns one embedding per sentence or segment. This removes the need to self-host the model."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import httpx, os\n\nJINA_API_KEY = os.environ[\"JINA_API_KEY\"]\n\ndef jina_late_chunking_embed(document: str) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Returns list of {text, embedding} dicts, one per sentence.\"\"\"\n    response = httpx.post(\n        \"https://api.jina.ai/v1/embeddings\",\n        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {JINA_API_KEY}\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n        json={\n            \"model\": \"jina-embeddings-v3\",\n            \"input\": [document],\n            \"task\": \"retrieval.passage\",\n            \"late_chunking\": True,   # key parameter \u2014 encode full doc, pool per sentence\n        },\n        timeout=60\n    )\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    data = response.json()\n    # Each item in data[\"data\"] is a sentence-level embedding\n    return [\n        {\"text\": doc[\"object\"], \"embedding\": doc[\"embedding\"]}\n        for doc in data[\"data\"]\n    ]\n\ndocument = open(\"paper.txt\").read()\nchunk_embeddings = jina_late_chunking_embed(document)\nprint(f\"Got {len(chunk_embeddings)} sentence embeddings via Jina late chunking API\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comparing Late Chunking to Contextual Retrieval"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Both late chunking and contextual retrieval (Anthropic's approach) address the same root problem \u2014 chunks losing their documentary context \u2014 but via different mechanisms and with different requirements."
          }
        ]
      },
